text.__SUMMARY__:
Acacia leptospermoides is a shrub belonging to the genus Acacia and the subgenus Phyllodineae. It is native to an area in the Great Southern, Wheatbelt and Mid West regions of Western Australia.The fleshy leafed shrub typically grows to a height of 0.1 to 2.0 metres (0.3 to 6.6 ft) and produces yellow flowers from June to September.
There are three subspecies

Acacia leptospermoides subsp. leptospermoides
Acacia leptospermoides subsp. obovata
Acacia leptospermoides subsp. psammophila
